<para0 verstatus="ver" security="u"><title>Scope Of the General Equipment
Manual</title>
<para>The General Equipment manual provides general information to
be used by maintenance personnel to further their understanding of
the aircraft and the installed systems. The manual provides organizational
maintenance information that is not adaptable to job guide format.</para>
</para0>
<para0 verstatus="ver" security="u"><title>Arrangement Of the General
Equipment Manual</title>
<para>The General Equipment manual is arranged by sections and subject
matter as follows:<deflist><title>TO 0X-00-0-00XX-00-1</title>
<term>Chapter 00</term><def>General Equipment Description</def>
<term>Chapter 1</term><def>Reserved</def>
<term>Chapter 2</term><def>Reserved</def>
<term>Chapter 3</term><def>Reserved</def>
<term>Chapter 4</term><def>Reserved</def>
<term>Chapter 5</term><def>Time Limits/Maintenance Checks</def>
<term>Chapter 6</term><def>Dimensions and Areas</def>
<term>Chapter 7</term><def>Lifting, Shoring, Recovering, and Transporting
</def>
<term>Chapter 8</term><def>Leveling and Weighing</def>
<term>Chapter 9</term><def>Towing and Taxiing</def>
<term>Chapter 10</term><def>Parking and Mooring</def>
<term>Chapter 11</term><def>Placards and Markings</def>
<term>Chapter 12</term><def>Servicing</def>
</deflist><deflist><title>TO 0X-00-0-00XX-00-2</title>
<term>Chapter 13</term><def>Wiring Repair and Electrical Maintenance
Procedures</def>
<term>Chapter 14</term><def>Circuit Breaker Panels, Overcurrent Protection
Panels, and Relay Matrices</def>
<term>Chapter 15</term><def>Non-destructive Inspection</def>
<term>Chapter 16</term><def>Siting Installation</def>
<term>Chapter 17</term><def>Preparation for Use and Shipment</def>
<term>Chapter 18</term><def>Weapons Instrumentation</def>
<term>Chapter 19</term><def>Training Equipment</def>
</deflist><deflist><title>TO 0X-00-0-00XX-00-3</title>
<term>Chapter 20</term><def>Test Chapter without any Sections</def>
<term>Chapter 21</term><def>Test Chapter without any Sections</def>
<term>Chapter 22</term><def>Test Chapter with Multiple Sections</def>
</deflist></para>
</para0>
<para0><title>USE OF THE General Equipment MANUAL</title>
<para>The General Equipment manual is used to familiarize the reader
with the aircraft, its configuration, and size as well as providing
a short general description of each system or subsystem installed
in the aircraft. A table of contents listing each section title and
major subject heading, a list of illustrations containing title and
figure number of each illustration, and a list of tables are located
in front of the manual.</para>
</para0>
<para0 verstatus="ver"><title>Use of "Shall", "Will", "Should", and
"May"</title>
<para>The word "shall" is used to express a provision that is binding.
 The words "should" and "may" are used when it is necessary to express
non-mandatory provisions.  The word "will" may be used to express
a mandatory declaration of purpose or when it is necessary to express
a future event. <applicabil applicref="a"></applicabil></para>
</para0>
<applicdef verstatus="ver"><title>List of Applicability and Effectivity</title>
<para>In this example the &ldquo;TERM&rdquo; heading is used to define
the column used for the symbol. The &ldquo;DEFINITION&rdquo; heading
is used to define the applicability/effectivity for the symbol used
in the &ldquo;TERM&rdquo; column.</para>
<appltitle>List of Applicability and Effectivity</appltitle>
<applichd>
<term>TERM</term><def>DEFINITION</def>
</applichd>
<applic id="a">
<term>a</term><def>This is applicability a. This could also contain
a listing of serial numbers as for an aircraft or to define applicability
to a part number.</def>
</applic>
<applic id="b">
<term>b</term><def>This is applicability b. This could also contain
a listing of serial numbers as for an aircraft or to define applicability
to a part number.</def>
</applic>
<applic id="c">
<term>c</term><def>This is applicability c. This could also contain
a listing of serial numbers as for an aircraft or to define applicability
to a part number.</def>
</applic>
<applic id="d">
<term>d</term><def>This is applicability d. This could also contain
a listing of serial numbers as for an aircraft or to define applicability
to a part number.</def>
</applic>
</applicdef>
